<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910319-0021</DOCNO><DOCID>910319-0021.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- CAE Industries Ltd.:   Unit Is Awarded Contract   By Pentagon for Simulator</HL><DATE>03/19/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C15</SO><CO>   T.CAE</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><LP>   CAE Industries Ltd. said its CAE-Link Corp. unit wasawarded a contract by the Pentagon to develop and build acombat mission simulator for the AH-64 Apache attackhelicopter for use by the Egyptian air force.   The contract has a value of 29 million Canadian dollars(US$25.2 million), CAE said.</LP><TEXT>   CAE said the simulator, scheduled for delivery in early1994, will be designed to train pilots to fly the latestversion of the AH-64 Apache and will include an advanceddigital visual system.   The Toronto company said the contract also includes spareparts and support equipment, maintenance training and twoyears of contractor logistics support.   CAE makes commercial and military aircraft simulators anddevelops related training systems.</TEXT></DOC>